### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It will handle routing, data reading/writing from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and serve the HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic (including data management, filtering, and page rendering) will be contained here.

- **requirements.txt**  
  Lists Python dependencies required to run the application (e.g., Flask or another lightweight web framework).

- **README.md**  
  Documentation file describing the project setup, running instructions, and overview.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the eight pages defined in the requirements. Each HTML file corresponds to one page:
  - `dashboard.html`: Dashboard page layout and elements.
  - `property_search.html`: Property search page with filters and property grid.
  - `property_details.html`: Detailed view of a single property.
  - `property_inquiry.html`: Form page for submitting inquiries.
  - `my_inquiries.html`: Page listing all user inquiries with status and management.
  - `my_favorites.html`: Page listing favorite properties with management options.
  - `agents.html`: Agent directory page.
  - `locations.html`: Featured locations page.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets:
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering).
  - `images/`: Folder for any images used in the app (property photos, agent photos).

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
  - `properties.txt`: Property listings data.
  - `locations.txt`: Location data.
  - `inquiries.txt`: Property inquiries data.
  - `favorites.txt`: Favorite properties data.
  - `agents.txt`: Real estate agents data.

This structure keeps the project organized, separates concerns clearly, and aligns with the requirement to use Python for backend and local text files for data storage."

